This paper deals with the problem of type inference in data, which is a common task in databases and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper proposes a probabilistic method, which involves statistical modeling and inference, making it relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with detecting anomalies and missing data, which are common problems in data science, making categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) relevant as well.
